Step 1 : Edit the homepage template
{% load static %}
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <meta name="description" content="Welcom to our restaurant!">
    <title>Restaurant Home</title>
    <link rel="stylesheet' href="{% static 'css/style.css' %}">
</head>
<body>
   <h1>Welcome to Our Restaurant</h>
   <p>Enjoy delicious meals and great ambiance.</p>
</body>
</html>

Step 2 : Why this helps SEO
1. Search engines use the meta description to show a short snippet in results.
2. Having a clear, keyword-rich decription increases click-through rate.
